# StandardModel.Charges

Electric charge, hypercharge, and color charge assignments.

Electric charge formula:
  Q = T₃ + Y/2  (Gell-Mann–Nishijima relation)

This module provides:
- The electric charge function Q for all SM particles
- Hypercharge assignments
- Color charge (Casimir) values
- Consistency lemmas (e.g., charge of W± is ±1)

Source: Gell-Mann and Nishijima (1956); Weinberg, "The Quantum Theory of Fields" Vol. 2.
Convention: Q = T₃ + Y/2 with the hypercharge values in `PhysicsSM.StandardModel.Fermions`.

Status: stub.
-/

